            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2405.03650/2405.03650v4/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2.High-Level Overviewof the proposed GCE framework during training. In Stage 1, the input scene graph is fed to theScene Graph EnricherGs​gG_{sg}, which produces an enriched scene graph. TheScene Graph CriticDs​gD_{sg}, implemented as a pair of local and global discriminators, provides adversarial training signals on the enriched scene graph. These training signals encourage the enriched scene graph to remain structurally coherent and semantically plausible. In Stage 2, theImage SynthesizerGi​mG_{im}renders an image from the enriched scene graph. In Stage 3, theVisual Scene CharacterizerSc​fS_{cf}and theImage-Text AlignerMi​m​_​s​gM_{im\\_sg}extract visual and text-alignment signals from the rendered image and the original scene information. Stage 3 is used only during training to encourage consistency; at inference, the learned enricher and renderer produce the output.",
                "position": 506
            }
        ]
